Instruction: Use a Virtual machine or a cloud-based linux instance for experimentation.
Install a software firewall like UFW(Uncomplicated Firewall) if not already installed.
Simulate the following tasks:
Allow incoming SSH traffic (port 22).
Allow incoming HTTP traffic (port 80).
Block all other incoming and outgoing traffic.

Commands:
#sudo apt install ufw
#sudo ufw allow 22/tcp
#sudo ufw allow 80/tcp
#sudo ufw default deny incoming
#sudo ufw default deny outgoing
#sudo ufw enable(this enables UFW)
#sudo ufw status(checks the status of UFW)
